WEBVTT

1
00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:32.740
"Who wants one more American
air base in the persian Gulf?"

2
00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:36.830
"Who wants occupation
by another name?"

3
00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:41.380
"Western imperialism by another name."

4
00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:44.686
"Who wants planes and helicopters

5
00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:46.000
flying over our children?"

6
00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:48.793
"Who wants to live -
under a foreign flag."

7
00:00:48.817 --> 00:00:49.106
Okay.

8
00:00:49.130 --> 00:00:51.906
What have I missed?
What's the interpreter saying?

9
00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:53.270
So far pretty vanilla.

10
00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:55.866
- The usual grievances…
- "we will never accept…".

11
00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:56.930
Di lenker?

12
00:00:57.520 --> 00:00:59.116
Bronze command. what do you see?

13
00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:00.706
Yep. there's no problem on the ground.

14
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:03.440
"This is the true face of
state-sponsored terrorism."

15
00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:07.376
"Let the occupiers pay
for the blood they shed."

16
00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:08.990
Okay. are you getting that?

17
00:01:09.650 --> 00:01:11.820
"Avenge this defilement
of a sovereign state."

18
00:01:12.360 --> 00:01:16.006
Cliff? You're the lawyer.
Anything we can charge?

19
00:01:16.030 --> 00:01:19.030
"Avenge" is not incitement
in and of itself. so…

20
00:01:22.210 --> 00:01:23.856
Gold command. be advised.

21
00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:25.720
Counterprotest gathering
on nails worth street.

22
00:01:30.170 --> 00:01:31.800
Okay. we knew this was coming.

23
00:01:32.430 --> 00:01:34.890
Unit c. hold them at the 80 yard cordon.

24
00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:37.720
Everyone else. eyes on the square.

25
00:01:39.890 --> 00:01:41.180
"An eye for an eye."

26
00:01:42.140 --> 00:01:43.376
"A life for a life."

27
00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:45.030
Right. does that clear the threshold?

28
00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:47.916
Death threat? Unlawful? Yes? No?

29
00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.546
The last time I checked. it wasn't
against the law to quote the quran

30
00:01:50.570 --> 00:01:52.046
or indeed the Bible.

31
00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.450
- Cliff. no one likes a smart-arse.
- Well. I do.

32
00:01:55.740 --> 00:01:57.756
June. how we looking?

33
00:01:57.780 --> 00:02:00.056
Yeah. it's still pretty calm.
There's no physical threat.

34
00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:02.830
Okay. well. discretion
up to a point. yeah?

35
00:02:03.580 --> 00:02:06.056
"Let our vengeance be
swift and without mercy…."

36
00:02:06.080 --> 00:02:09.290
Unit Charlie to gold command.
we have 50 men at the outer cordon.

37
00:02:10.510 --> 00:02:13.316
Okay. but is the area secure?

38
00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:14.880
Secure for now. over.

39
00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:18.326
"Let these animals pay for their insult…."

40
00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:20.406
Well. that's not holy text surely.

41
00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:21.706
Right. so enough to arrest?

42
00:02:21.730 --> 00:02:26.496
It has to be a targeted threat against
a named individual or individuals.

43
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:27.520
Cliff.

44
00:02:31.990 --> 00:02:34.676
Unit Charlie to gold
command. significant presence.

45
00:02:34.700 --> 00:02:37.450
75 meters down from the
square. it's getting pretty hot.

46
00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:40.386
That sounds close…

47
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:43.290
Where is that? Is that nails worth street?

48
00:02:47.040 --> 00:02:49.080
"Get organized. Cut
the head off the snake."

49
00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:51.606
Call to action?

50
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:53.566
"Any American diplomats
and apologists…."

51
00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.526
- Yes.
- Targeted call to violence?

52
00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:57.696
- Yes.
- Is that enough to escalate?

53
00:02:57.720 --> 00:02:58.776
I would say. "yes."

54
00:02:58.800 --> 00:03:00.696
Right. so we are clear to arrest?

55
00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:02.786
Section 44. You have grounds for arrest.

56
00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:04.650
Right. and is that your recommendation?

57
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:08.456
Yep. yeah. Confirmed yes.

58
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.626
Okay. And is it just the
leader or all of them?

59
00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:13.320
Because some of them are
just… some of them are just kids.

60
00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:16.950
Hold it together!

61
00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.740
Let's go!

62
00:03:22.700 --> 00:03:23.766
Fuck!

63
00:03:23.790 --> 00:03:25.436
Urgent tactical support required. Repeat.

64
00:03:25.460 --> 00:03:27.396
- All… urgent…
- recommend…

65
00:03:27.420 --> 00:03:30.766
Yeah. I'm sorry. ma'am. I can't…
I can't hear you. Can you repeat?

66
00:03:30.790 --> 00:03:33.106
Just the leader at present
so we can review the tapes…

67
00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:35.946
- Okay. You're clear to arrest the leader.
- Mike. Sierra. Mike. Sierra.

68
00:03:35.970 --> 00:03:37.100
Arrest authorized.

69
00:03:40.180 --> 00:03:42.770
Breach. breach! They're
heading towards the square!

70
00:03:57.910 --> 00:04:01.080
Urgent tactical support
needed. All units…

71
00:04:01.910 --> 00:04:03.636
In! In. in. in!

72
00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:05.750
Break it up! Break it up!

73
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.350
Get back!

74
00:04:23.760 --> 00:04:25.180
Get out the way!

75
00:04:38.950 --> 00:04:41.120
Help! Somebody. help!

76
00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:45.176
Out the way. Okay.

77
00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:46.556
Okay. Come here.

78
00:04:46.580 --> 00:04:47.790
Paramedics!

79
00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:50.266
You his friend. yeah?

80
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.816
- You see here? Your hand here.
- Back. back! Everyone back!

81
00:04:52.840 --> 00:04:54.720
Press down hard. Look
at me. Press down hard.

82
00:04:55.880 --> 00:04:57.896
Okay. All right.

83
00:04:57.920 --> 00:04:59.760
My god. All right.

84
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:02.720
Where are the paramedics?

85
00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:06.600
I've got you.

86
00:05:07.470 --> 00:05:10.470
All right. Look at me.
You're fine. I've got you.

87
00:05:12.150 --> 00:05:14.770
Mum.

88
00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:16.506
Mum.

89
00:05:16.530 --> 00:05:18.006
- I've got you. I've got you.
- Mum.

90
00:05:18.030 --> 00:05:19.450
You're gonna see your mum.

91
00:05:34.590 --> 00:05:38.220
When I think of you

92
00:05:41.430 --> 00:05:48.060
my heart remembers

93
00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:57.240
all the love we've ever had
all the love we've ever had

94
00:05:57.820 --> 00:06:01.280
just me and you

95
00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:09.410
when I think of you

96
00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:20.380
just me and you just me
and you just me and you.

97
00:06:25.890 --> 00:06:27.776
Thank you. Thank you. everybody.

98
00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:29.366
Please all take your seats.

99
00:06:29.390 --> 00:06:33.390
Before we begin. an urgent
question from margo Whitaker. mp.

100
00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:36.730
Fifteen years old.

101
00:06:37.810 --> 00:06:41.480
Just a regular lad from my constituency.

102
00:06:42.610 --> 00:06:44.216
My backyard.

103
00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:46.200
- Cheers. mate.
- No worries.

104
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.120
Hi. can I get a pen please?

105
00:06:50.990 --> 00:06:54.136
He only came along because. I quote.

106
00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:58.566
"there was room in the Van. and
he wanted to go on the London eye."

107
00:06:58.590 --> 00:07:03.140
Now. I see from the news you
are appealing for witnesses?

108
00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:06.776
Thanks.

109
00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:09.786
May I suggest you start with the 34
officers stood around like lemmings

110
00:07:09.810 --> 00:07:11.576
whilst a boy was stabbed
to death in front of you?

111
00:07:11.600 --> 00:07:15.076
It's our understanding that
the nails worth street rally

112
00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:17.126
was infiltrated at the 11th hour

113
00:07:17.150 --> 00:07:21.410
by a small cell of up to
six extremist individuals.

114
00:07:22.110 --> 00:07:23.916
Their faces covered.

115
00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:26.506
unknown to the others. they
came with the sole intention...

116
00:07:26.530 --> 00:07:30.620
not one… not one of this cell
have you been able to identify.

117
00:07:31.540 --> 00:07:36.436
Your job. last time I
looked. is to stop crime.

118
00:07:36.460 --> 00:07:41.800
And yet no arrests. no
witnesses and no murder weapon.

119
00:07:44.010 --> 00:07:47.390
Is it any wonder public confidence
in the police is rock bottom?

120
00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:30.850
Who is she. and what's she doing here?

121
00:08:31.350 --> 00:08:32.520
I'm…

122
00:08:34.010 --> 00:08:36.180
I just wanted to say.
I'm so sorry for your loss.

123
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:43.770
He's saying.

124
00:08:45.110 --> 00:08:46.400
"what do you want?"

125
00:08:51.570 --> 00:08:52.740
I was with him. I was there.

126
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:54.990
Your son.

127
00:08:55.950 --> 00:08:59.596
And I just… I wish I could've stopped it.

128
00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:00.830
Please go.

129
00:09:02.290 --> 00:09:04.080
Please. just someone make her go.

130
00:09:04.880 --> 00:09:06.396
It's okay.

131
00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:07.960
Sorry. I'm so sorry.

132
00:09:16.850 --> 00:09:18.746
- Can I have some?
- Di lenker?

133
00:09:18.770 --> 00:09:20.706
Yeah. it's still pretty calm.
There's no physical threat.

134
00:09:20.730 --> 00:09:22.496
Urgent tactical support required. Repeat.

135
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:24.706
All units. urgent tactical support required.

136
00:09:24.730 --> 00:09:26.410
Where is that? Is that nails worth street?

137
00:09:28.740 --> 00:09:30.756
- Mum.
- Where are the paramedics?

138
00:09:30.780 --> 00:09:32.886
Mum. Mum.

139
00:09:32.910 --> 00:09:35.120
- I've got you. I've got you.
- Mum.

140
00:10:06.150 --> 00:10:07.320
Thanks. Jerry.

141
00:10:16.200 --> 00:10:19.790
- Tony.
- Who are you?

142
00:10:20.910 --> 00:10:21.910
It's me.

143
00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:24.050
Dan. the gaffer.

144
00:10:26.130 --> 00:10:29.316
"The gaffer?" You sure? Fuckin' temerity.

145
00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:31.090
For Christ's sake. Tony.

146
00:10:33.220 --> 00:10:34.550
I'm not that far gone.

147
00:10:35.970 --> 00:10:37.616
Yeah. you should see
old Jim through the wall.

148
00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:39.390
He's on a drip and a respirator and…

149
00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:42.390
They still reckon he's a flight risk.

150
00:10:44.900 --> 00:10:47.206
You look like shit. Don't tell
me it's that daughter of yours.

151
00:10:47.230 --> 00:10:49.506
What's her name? Lulu or Louisa...

152
00:10:49.530 --> 00:10:50.956
- Lisa.
- Yeah. what's the latest?

153
00:10:50.980 --> 00:10:52.666
Is she still up north? Isle of…

154
00:10:52.690 --> 00:10:54.376
- Was it isle of eigg?
- Findhorn.

155
00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:56.360
Findhorn. Nice.

156
00:10:57.620 --> 00:11:00.846
Plenty of clapped-out old hippies
up there to keep her warm at night.

157
00:11:00.870 --> 00:11:01.870
Listen.

158
00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:04.250
I just wanted to kick
the tires on something.

159
00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:06.686
Here it comes. The ulterior motive.

160
00:11:06.710 --> 00:11:07.816
Yeah. Crack on.

161
00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:10.976
Something you said a while back.

162
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:12.000
What did I say?

163
00:11:13.130 --> 00:11:14.130
This guy.

164
00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:16.800
Cosmo Thompson.

165
00:11:19.350 --> 00:11:20.350
I see.

166
00:11:21.310 --> 00:11:23.116
You said he was nothing. Small time.

167
00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:24.140
Yeah.

168
00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:26.390
Well. I changed my mind.

169
00:11:32.530 --> 00:11:35.836
Now. I gather you're keen
to help with the investigation.

170
00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:38.136
Well. I was there. So. yeah.
of course I want to help.

171
00:11:38.160 --> 00:11:41.386
Well. Mike and his team
downstairs are more than competent

172
00:11:41.410 --> 00:11:43.386
- to handle things. Okay?
- I'm not saying they're not.

173
00:11:43.410 --> 00:11:45.766
They don't need you marking
their homework for them.

174
00:11:45.790 --> 00:11:47.596
But you've got a lot of friends here. June.

175
00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:50.170
so no one's throwing you to
the wolves. Not while I'm here.

176
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:52.026
Let me tell you.

177
00:11:52.050 --> 00:11:55.646
the person responsible
for the death of that lad

178
00:11:55.670 --> 00:11:59.220
is the individual who stuck
a six-inch blade in his chest.

179
00:11:59.930 --> 00:12:01.576
And whoever that is.
we will run 'em down.

180
00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:05.100
And when we do. all this
name-calling and finger-jabbing.

181
00:12:05.730 --> 00:12:07.036
it'll come to an end. Okay?

182
00:12:07.060 --> 00:12:09.786
But until then. we've
just gotta put up with it.

183
00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:11.940
- So leave Mike and his team to it. yeah?
- Yeah.

184
00:12:12.480 --> 00:12:14.296
- Yeah?
- Yes.

185
00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:16.780
Good. That's pep talk over.

186
00:12:19.740 --> 00:12:21.306
In the meantime.

187
00:12:21.330 --> 00:12:23.716
no further contact with
the victim's family. I would...

188
00:12:23.740 --> 00:12:25.516
sorry. Can I ask why?

189
00:12:25.540 --> 00:12:28.516
- Just erring on the side of…
- caution?

190
00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:29.670
Right.

191
00:12:30.290 --> 00:12:32.580
So give your statement
and move on. okay?

192
00:12:33.090 --> 00:12:35.606
I want you kept well
away from the blast radius.

193
00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:37.026
Okay.

194
00:12:37.050 --> 00:12:38.050
Very good.

195
00:12:44.810 --> 00:12:45.866
Here you go.

196
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:47.230
Okay. picture round.

197
00:12:58.150 --> 00:13:00.150
- Is this all you've got?
- Afraid so.

198
00:13:00.780 --> 00:13:02.620
Waiting on cctv analysis.

199
00:13:04.240 --> 00:13:06.830
Plenty of witnesses. but nothing of value.

200
00:13:23.850 --> 00:13:25.270
Can I take this one?

201
00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:56.936
It's three days since violence erupted

202
00:13:56.960 --> 00:13:59.146
at Suffolk square in central London.

203
00:13:59.170 --> 00:14:02.736
causing the death of a teenage
boy as well as countless injuries.

204
00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:05.986
Tonight. we ask what the
police could have done differently.

205
00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:10.260
and whether it's time to start treating
homegrown extremists as terrorists.

206
00:14:34.460 --> 00:14:37.356
Billy fielding arrived in court.
where he was sentenced

207
00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:40.680
to 17 years for killing
his girlfriend. cerys Jones.

208
00:14:41.970 --> 00:14:46.406
A statement was read outside on
behalf of cerys's mother. Ashley Jones.

209
00:14:46.430 --> 00:14:50.116
While today's judgment
goes some way to bring justice

210
00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:52.940
for the murder of my daughter. cerys.

211
00:14:53.850 --> 00:14:56.496
there is nothing that
can ever bring her back

212
00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:59.310
or make up for her loss from this world.

213
00:14:59.980 --> 00:15:02.716
Cerys was 16 years old.

214
00:15:02.740 --> 00:15:05.426
She had her whole life in front of her.

215
00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:09.200
Every day I have to
remind myself she is gone.

216
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:44.480
Ashley?

217
00:15:45.860 --> 00:15:47.386
Ashley Jones?

218
00:15:47.410 --> 00:15:50.080
This is di June lenker. Can
you open the door please?

219
00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:57.120
Okay.

220
00:15:58.290 --> 00:15:59.290
All right.

221
00:16:01.090 --> 00:16:02.090
Ashley.

222
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:16.680
Ashley?

223
00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:29.200
Hello?

224
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:31.740
Ashley?

225
00:16:32.910 --> 00:16:35.370
Ashley? Ashley?

226
00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:38.540
Can you hear me?

227
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.710
Hello. Ashley?

228
00:16:41.790 --> 00:16:43.936
Hi. yeah. I need an ambulance.

229
00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:46.026
I've got an unresponsive female.

230
00:16:46.050 --> 00:16:47.720
It's 20 west view court off dalston Lane.

231
00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:49.776
Hang on.

232
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.800
No. Fine. Cancel.

233
00:16:52.510 --> 00:16:53.510
You okay?

234
00:16:57.640 --> 00:16:58.640
Okay.

235
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.496
Yeah. sorry about that.

236
00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:05.320
Ashley. have you swallowed anything
else apart from the metapotrozine?

237
00:17:05.690 --> 00:17:06.876
- No.
- No?

238
00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:09.886
- Sorry. It's just…
- that's okay.

239
00:17:09.910 --> 00:17:11.846
It calms me down. You know?

240
00:17:11.870 --> 00:17:13.910
Yeah. All right. Let's…

241
00:17:14.790 --> 00:17:16.516
Should we get you some help?

242
00:17:16.540 --> 00:17:19.040
Yeah. I was gonna have a bath though.

243
00:17:20.170 --> 00:17:21.170
Yeah.

244
00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:02.896
Lovely pull. that.

245
00:18:02.920 --> 00:18:04.646
- You know I don't like this flavor.
- Go on. cosmo.

246
00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:06.106
- Is it hot?
- Stick it down his…

247
00:18:06.130 --> 00:18:08.220
- Is it a bit hot? Is it a bit hot?
- Will you stop…

248
00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:13.616
Give me some good
news for Christ's sake.

249
00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:15.020
No such luck.

250
00:18:15.550 --> 00:18:17.116
Three guesses what I'm looking at.

251
00:18:17.140 --> 00:18:19.196
- Go on.
- Give us a clue.

252
00:18:19.220 --> 00:18:20.576
It's mad.

253
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:21.826
That's not a clue.

254
00:18:21.850 --> 00:18:25.100
All right. then. It's a…
it's a blast from the past.

255
00:18:25.860 --> 00:18:27.240
That narrows it down a bit.

256
00:18:32.910 --> 00:18:34.700
You are gonna love this.

257
00:18:51.340 --> 00:18:52.670
You all right back there?

258
00:18:53.180 --> 00:18:54.680
