378
00:26:12.200 --> 00:26:14.136
Maggie. Maggie.

379
00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:16.386
- Fragrant Maggie.
- "Fragrant."

380
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:18.636
- I don't… I don't blame you. you know?
- I mean. what?

381
00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:22.516
She's… she's like
Yoda with amazing hair.

382
00:26:22.540 --> 00:26:23.896
Well. yeah.

383
00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:26.146
I guess. if you're gonna put it like that…

384
00:26:26.170 --> 00:26:27.920
- So predictable.
- …Then maybe I do.

385
00:26:30.470 --> 00:26:32.600
I was thinking maybe we
could do something tonight.

386
00:26:34.220 --> 00:26:35.600
Jacob's with his dad.

387
00:26:37.140 --> 00:26:39.430
- Yeah. Like what?
- Cheap night in?

388
00:26:40.980 --> 00:26:42.246
Ever the romantic.

389
00:26:42.270 --> 00:26:43.520
Or. I don't know. we could…

390
00:26:44.650 --> 00:26:47.740
Get a drink. go to a bar. People watch.

391
00:26:50.240 --> 00:26:51.280
June?

392
00:26:54.030 --> 00:26:55.280
June. you okay?

393
00:26:56.160 --> 00:26:57.160
Yeah.

394
00:26:58.620 --> 00:26:59.870
just give me a minute.

395
00:27:23.690 --> 00:27:25.030
I'm sorry about your trouble.

396
00:27:25.770 --> 00:27:26.836
My what?

397
00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:28.780
First time as sio in the wild.

398
00:27:29.530 --> 00:27:32.086
Leading the line against
a crowd of headbangers.

399
00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:33.570
Not quite the first time. but…

400
00:27:34.150 --> 00:27:36.296
It's tough. Tough going.

401
00:27:36.320 --> 00:27:38.176
Sorry. I'm not meaning
to pick at your scabs.

402
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:39.580
- Sure.
- You're okay though?

403
00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:41.620
Yeah.

404
00:27:42.540 --> 00:27:43.976
How about you? You all right?

405
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:45.000
Yeah.

406
00:27:45.540 --> 00:27:47.920
Same old. you know.
Eighth floor looking after you?

407
00:27:49.170 --> 00:27:50.856
They're being pretty supportive. actually.

408
00:27:50.880 --> 00:27:52.316
Good.

409
00:27:52.340 --> 00:27:55.930
It's good to hear. Least they
can do under the circumstances.

410
00:27:56.970 --> 00:27:58.026
What does that mean?

411
00:27:58.050 --> 00:27:59.590
Zero planning.

412
00:28:00.350 --> 00:28:04.400
Tactical balls up. Political pressure.
no doubt. but that's on them…

413
00:28:05.350 --> 00:28:06.980
- Yeah.
- …Not you.

414
00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:11.480
Well. thanks for that.

415
00:28:13.280 --> 00:28:14.280
So…

416
00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:17.440
This guy. Billy fielding.

417
00:28:20.780 --> 00:28:21.780
Right.

418
00:28:22.370 --> 00:28:24.500
It's work. It's not personal.

419
00:28:25.250 --> 00:28:27.710
- I heard you retired.
- Nah. where would I go?

420
00:28:29.710 --> 00:28:31.040
No. they moved me

421
00:28:32.380 --> 00:28:33.800
to intelligence.

422
00:28:36.180 --> 00:28:37.890
So I'm just asking for a friend.

423
00:28:40.010 --> 00:28:41.390
What's your interest?

424
00:28:42.310 --> 00:28:43.480
"My interest"?

425
00:28:45.060 --> 00:28:48.126
Well. I suppose my
first question would be.

426
00:28:48.150 --> 00:28:51.650
"since when were the prison
service such fucking terrible liars?"

427
00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:55.900
Where is he? Fielding? Is he out?

428
00:28:56.700 --> 00:28:57.950
What's on your mind?

429
00:29:06.080 --> 00:29:07.936
- Suffolk square.
- Your thing?

430
00:29:07.960 --> 00:29:10.396
- My thing.
- No prizes for best photographer.

431
00:29:10.420 --> 00:29:13.436
Look. if you're just gonna sit
there and deny it… I was there.

432
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:14.686
So. I saw him.

433
00:29:14.710 --> 00:29:15.920
You saw him?

434
00:29:17.130 --> 00:29:19.946
- Yeah.
- And have you told Mike about this notion?

435
00:29:19.970 --> 00:29:22.236
- "Notion"?
- Or anyone else on his team?

436
00:29:22.260 --> 00:29:23.366
Did you. June. did you?

437
00:29:23.390 --> 00:29:24.980
No. Not yet. Why?

438
00:29:30.270 --> 00:29:31.270
What's going on here?

439
00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:44.950
You'll find these are a better angle.

440
00:30:06.310 --> 00:30:07.310
So. it is him?

441
00:30:08.810 --> 00:30:09.890
It's him?

442
00:30:11.600 --> 00:30:14.350
- But how… how… how is he even…
- he broke out.

443
00:30:14.980 --> 00:30:15.980
Friday night.

444
00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:18.796
Catering truck exits through the gates.

445
00:30:18.820 --> 00:30:21.466
security's short-staffed so
nobody checked underneath.

446
00:30:21.490 --> 00:30:22.886
Can you believe?

447
00:30:22.910 --> 00:30:26.080
- He was hiding under the truck?
- God bless the prison service.

448
00:30:27.370 --> 00:30:29.000
Why isn't this on the news?

449
00:30:31.620 --> 00:30:32.750
Circle of trust?

450
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:36.566
Think about it.

451
00:30:36.590 --> 00:30:40.396
Prison staff report he's gone
early hours of Saturday morning.

452
00:30:40.420 --> 00:30:42.026
A few hours back and forth.

453
00:30:42.050 --> 00:30:45.076
Panic. Blame game. The police
think they've got him. "No. We haven't."

454
00:30:45.100 --> 00:30:48.446
They're finally putting a statement
together when your thing happened.

455
00:30:48.470 --> 00:30:49.760
Suffolk square.

456
00:30:50.680 --> 00:30:52.536
And. you know. the
view from the politburo is…

457
00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:54.206
- Two stories?
- Same weekend.

458
00:30:54.230 --> 00:30:55.836
A prison break and a stabbing?

459
00:30:55.860 --> 00:30:57.086
Institutionally. it's…

460
00:30:57.110 --> 00:31:00.110
- Unsurvivable.
- Tough. Yeah. maybe so.

461
00:31:00.740 --> 00:31:04.140
Plus. of course. there's. "fingers crossed
we get him quick. No one's any the wiser."

462
00:31:05.910 --> 00:31:07.870
What are we on now? Day four?

463
00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:09.660
Five.

464
00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:15.380
So. I've been wheeled
in for analytic support.

465
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:17.460
Always a desperate sign.

466
00:31:18.880 --> 00:31:22.380
But if he's on the run. what is
he doing in the center of a riot?

467
00:31:28.890 --> 00:31:30.230
Why are you telling me all this?

468
00:31:33.190 --> 00:31:36.400
Well. we're in the same boat.

469
00:31:37.900 --> 00:31:39.360
Same interest. This guy here.

470
00:31:39.940 --> 00:31:41.836
He's a key witness for your murder.

471
00:31:41.860 --> 00:31:44.240
And. as for me. I just want
him back where he belongs.

472
00:31:44.990 --> 00:31:46.086
In prison?

473
00:31:46.110 --> 00:31:47.150
Aye.

474
00:31:49.540 --> 00:31:50.540
And that's it?

475
00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:55.396
My point is. if this thing gets out.

476
00:31:55.420 --> 00:31:58.226
Mike. investigation. public appeal.

477
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:00.590
Billy fielding goes to
ground. we'll never get him.

478
00:32:03.340 --> 00:32:04.340
So…

479
00:32:06.340 --> 00:32:07.340
You help me.

480
00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:09.406
I mean it.

481
00:32:09.430 --> 00:32:11.536
You help me run him down.

482
00:32:11.560 --> 00:32:12.866
We do it our way.

483
00:32:12.890 --> 00:32:15.116
And when we do. you talk to him.

484
00:32:15.140 --> 00:32:17.376
Interview. Suffolk square.

485
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:19.456
What was he doing
there? Was he armed?

486
00:32:19.480 --> 00:32:21.820
Who was he with? Names. faces.

487
00:32:23.490 --> 00:32:25.410
You want me to work for you?

488
00:32:26.450 --> 00:32:27.660
Change of scene.

489
00:32:28.490 --> 00:32:30.280
You make it sound like a mini-break.

490
00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:31.990
No.

491
00:32:32.620 --> 00:32:34.290
It's better than a mini-break.

492
00:32:42.590 --> 00:32:44.486
Are you fucking shitting me?

493
00:32:44.510 --> 00:32:45.736
Hegarty?

494
00:32:45.760 --> 00:32:49.850
- Look. maybe this is what I need?
- "What you need"? That twat? No. no.

495
00:32:50.390 --> 00:32:54.390
- Self-help is not a good look on you.
- I knew you were gonna be like this.

496
00:32:55.600 --> 00:32:56.666
Yeah.

497
00:32:56.690 --> 00:32:59.416
'Cause I've got an
actual brain. More or less.

498
00:32:59.440 --> 00:33:00.980
What's Leo got to say about all this?

499
00:33:01.770 --> 00:33:03.310
Well. I…

500
00:33:05.150 --> 00:33:06.216
Of course.

501
00:33:06.240 --> 00:33:10.886
- You haven't told him. Nice.
- No. I will… I will tell him.

502
00:33:10.910 --> 00:33:13.016
- Right.
- It's just… what?

503
00:33:13.040 --> 00:33:16.266
No. Nothing. Just… just
looking out for my psycho friend.

504
00:33:16.290 --> 00:33:17.540
Then stop yelling at her.

505
00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:26.680
- What you doing?
- I'm… I'm driving. I'm making it last.

506
00:33:28.010 --> 00:33:29.066
Right. Listen.

507
00:33:29.090 --> 00:33:31.276
There's something I've gotta
say. so I'm just gonna say it.

508
00:33:31.300 --> 00:33:33.800
I'm getting weirdly nervous now.

509
00:33:34.770 --> 00:33:36.980
What happened at Suffolk square…

510
00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:40.416
It made me so angry.

511
00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:45.320
It was a fucking disgrace.
but it is not your disgrace.

512
00:33:53.370 --> 00:33:54.450
Oi.

513
00:33:54.950 --> 00:33:55.990
What?

514
00:33:57.120 --> 00:33:58.250
Got a bit going on?

515
00:34:00.330 --> 00:34:01.330
Yeah.

516
00:34:02.880 --> 00:34:03.880
Yeah.

517
00:34:06.550 --> 00:34:09.090
It's just… yeah.

518
00:34:09.720 --> 00:34:11.350
- I know...
- no. you don't know.

519
00:34:15.930 --> 00:34:19.706
He keeps calling me. and he
left me a really long message.

520
00:34:19.730 --> 00:34:21.940
- Who… who keeps calling?
- The grandad.

521
